quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  87,1,"Glorify the name of your Lord, the Most High,",footnotes:182672:1
  87,2,"Who created all things and fashioned them in good proportion;",footnotes:182673:1
  87,3,"Who determined and guided them,",footnotes:182674:1|182675:2
  87,4,"Who brought forth the pasture,",footnotes:182676:1
  87,5,"and then made it into a blackish straw.",footnotes:182677:1
  87,6,"We shall make you recite and then you will not forget,",footnotes:182678:1
  87,7,"except what Allah should wish. He knows all that is manifest and all that is hidden.",footnotes:182679:1|182680:2
  87,8,"We shall ease you to follow the way of Ease."
  87,9,"So render good counsel if good counsel will avail.",footnotes:182681:1
  87,10,"He who fears (Allah) shall heed it,",footnotes:182682:1
  87,11,"but the wretched will turn away from it."
  87,12,"He will be cast into the Great Fire."
  87,13,"Then he will neither die in it, nor live.",footnotes:182683:1
  87,14,"He who purified himself shall prosper,",footnotes:182684:1
  87,15,"remembering his Lord's name and praying.",footnotes:182685:1|182686:2
  87,16,"No; but you prefer the present life,",footnotes:182687:1
  87,17,"whereas the Hereafter is better and more enduring.",footnotes:182688:1
  87,18,"This, indeed, was in the ancient Scrolls,"
  87,19,"the Scrolls of Abraham and Moses.",footnotes:182689:1
